# Lens Studio {{VERSION}} Project Reference

This project uses Lens Studio. Scripts can be written in JavaScript (ES2019 compliant) or TypeScript.

Important Notes:

- The global execution context is the `script` object in JavaScript, or `this` in TypeScript components.
- UI inputs are defined using comment-based decorators (`// @input`) in JavaScript, or `@input` decorators in TypeScript.
- Do not use `window` or `document` objects; this is a unique runtime, not a browser.
- All components must extend `BaseScriptComponent` in TypeScript.
- Lens Studio uses a **right-handed coordinate system**: +X is right, +Y is up, -Z is forward.
- World units are in **centimeters** (cm) and **degrees** (however, many APIs operate in radians).
- Always work with files inside the `Assets/` directory — this is where all project resources live.
- Never modify files in the `Cache/` directory — it contains auto-generated/cached data that is regenerated by Lens Studio.
- The **Lens API** (StudioLib) and the **Editor API** (editor.d.ts) are two completely separate APIs for different purposes. The **Lens API** is the language for building AR experiences — use it for all lens project scripts (TypeScript or JavaScript). The **Editor API** is only for controlling the Lens Studio application itself — use it only when you need to interact with the app (e.g., modify settings, perform app actions). Editor API scripts must be written in **JavaScript only**.

## Documentation

- [Lens API Reference](Support/{{STUDIOLIB_PATH}}): TypeScript definitions for the **Lens scripting API** — the language for building AR experiences. Use this for all lens project scripts (TypeScript or JavaScript).
- [Editor API Reference](Support/editor.d.ts): TypeScript definitions for the **Lens Studio Editor API** — for controlling the Lens Studio application itself (performing actions, modifying settings, checking statuses). Only use this when you need to interact with the Lens Studio app, not for building lenses. **Editor API scripts must be written in JavaScript only, never TypeScript.**
- [Scripting Guide](.agents/LensStudio/scripting_guide.md): Core syntax for Inputs, Events, and exposing APIs between scripts.
- [Common API Cheatsheet](.agents/LensStudio/api_cheatsheet.md): Essential classes for manipulating Transforms, SceneObjects, and Components.
- [Project Structure](.agents/LensStudio/structure.md): How Lens Studio projects organize resources and objects.

## Optional

- [Performance Best Practices](.agents/LensStudio/performance.md): Guidelines for frame-rate optimization and texture memory usage.
